-- Bridgepoint Close to Acquiring Two French Jewelry Retailers, Times Reports
-- Jonathan Browning
-- 2010-08-01T07:53:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-01/bridgepoint-close-to-acquiring-two-french-jewelry-retailers-times-reports.html

          
          
             Bridgepoint Capital Ltd. is in
advanced talks to buy French jewelery retailers Histoire d’Or
and Marc Orian from private-equity groups for a total of 600
million euros ($783 million), the Sunday Times reported.  
 The U.K. buyout firm would merge the two chains to create a
company with 300 outlets and 350 million euros in sales, the
newspaper reported, without saying where it got the information.
Histoire d’Or is owned by Silverfleet Capital Ltd., and Marc
Orian is owned by Qualium Investissement.  
